properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS - SYDNEY Bradfield Highway at Sydney Harbour Bridge
properties.otherAdvice:
There will be a short term closure of all southbound lanes approaching the Harbour Bridge including the Cahill Expressway between 8:10am and 8:30am approximately while vintage cars travel across the bridge in a Police escorted convoy for the Sydney Harbour Bridge 90th Anniversary event.

Motorists travelling southbound will be diverted into the Harbour Tunnel during this time. Oversize (over 4.4m) & Dangerous Goods Vehicles will need to travel via the Gladesville Bridge and Victoria Rd during this time.

Lane 4 northbound on the Sydney Harbour Bridge will also be closed and the speed limit will be reduced to 40km/h across the bridge. Northbound traffic will remain unaffected and can continue across the Harbour Bridge in lanes 1-3.
